4. DISSERTATION TEXT DRAFT
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Contrary to expectation, the deep hedger shows L2 gradient norm 23.748 versus 23.119 for BS delta (ratio 0.97). The deep hedger is at least as sensitive as BS along the tested axes. At |eps|=0.060 on the H axis, BS degrades by +4.9% and DH by +8.9%. At |eps|=0.060 on the H axis, BS degrades by -10.5% and DH by -10.9%. At |eps|=1.400 on the eta axis, BS degrades by -63.0% and DH by -60.3%. Hypothesis H3 is REFUTED at this calibration. This is consistent with the decomposition from §6.3.2: a strategy whose advantage is objective-driven has no particular reason to be robust to dynamic misspecification.
